msgid ""
"The `exchangeToMono()` and `exchangeToFlux()` methods (or `awaitExchange { "
"}` and `exchangeToFlow { }` in Kotlin)  are useful for more advanced cases "
"that require more control, such as to decode the response differently "
"depending on the response status:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/web/webflux-webclient/client-exchange.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "Java"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/web/webflux-webclient/client-exchange.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tMono<Person> entityMono = client.get()\n"
"\t\t\t.uri(\"/persons/1\")\n"
"\t\t\t.accept(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n"
"\t\t\t.exchangeToMono(response -> {\n"
"\t\t\t\tif (response.statusCode().equals(HttpStatus.OK)) {\n"
"\t\t\t\t\treturn response.bodyToMono(Person.class);\n"
"\t\t\t\t}\n"
"\t\t\t\telse {\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t// Turn to error\n"
"\t\t\t\t\treturn response.createError();\n"
"\t\t\t\t}\n"
"\t\t\t});\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/web/webflux-webclient/client-exchange.adoc:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "Kotlin"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/web/webflux-webclient/client-exchange.adoc:43
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"val entity = client.get()\n"
"  .uri(\"/persons/1\")\n"
"  .accept(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n"
"  .awaitExchange {\n"
"\t\tif (response.statusCode() == HttpStatus.OK) {\n"
"\t\t\t return response.awaitBody<Person>()\n"
"\t\t}\n"
"\t\telse {\n"
"\t\t\t throw response.createExceptionAndAwait()\n"
"\t\t}\n"
"  }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/web/webflux-webclient/client-exchange.adoc:49
msgid ""
"When using the above, after the returned `Mono` or `Flux` completes, the "
"response body is checked and if not consumed it is released to prevent "
"memory and connection leaks.  Therefore the response cannot be decoded "
"further downstream. It is up to the provided function to declare how to "
"decode the response if needed."
msgstr ""
